#1 Resected metastatic colon adenocarcinoma (T3, N0, M1 [liver])
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Drs. Delaney and Ricketts service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Collins, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
We have recommended additional systemic chemotherapy.  Mrs. Martinez does plan on receiving additional treatment closer to home, but we would recommend that she return in the outpatient setting for evaluation.  She wishes to return.  Therefore, I have made follow-up arrangements for the patient to return in approximately four weeks.  At that time, she will undergo a CT-scan of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis, comprehensive lab panel including a CEA, and an appointment with Dr. Jamie Sanchez in Medical Oncology as well as a postoperative evaluation with Drs. Andrews and Zhang.  She will also make contact with Dr. Parker, her local medical oncologist, and ensure that an appointment follows ours to make sure there is continuity of care and she is initiated on additional chemotherapy in a timely fashion.  She verbalized understanding and wishes to proceed.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

